{"lemma":"بَدَنِ","slug":"بَدَنِ","root":"ب.د.ن","root_slug":"ب-د-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-د-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَدَن","root":"بدن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":8,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2014","n2015","n2016","n2017","n2018","n2019"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"body; figure","examples":[{"text":"وكتب الحجّاج بن يوسف إلى الحكم بن أيّوب قال: اخطب على عبد الملك امرأةً جميلةً من بعيدٍ، مليحةً من قريبٍ، شريفةً في قومها، ذليلةً في نفسها، أمةً لبعلها. . فكتب إليه: أصبتها، وهي خولة بنت مسمع، لولا عظم ثديها! فكتب إليه الحجّاج: لا يحسن بدن المرأة حتّى يعظم ثدياها فتدفي الضّجيع، وتروي الرّضيع.","english":"Al-Ḥajjāj once wrote to al-Ḥakam ibn ʾAyyūb, \"Pledge to ʿAbd al-Malik a woman who looks pretty from afar and sweet up close, who is of noble birth and humble soul, a slave to her husband.\" The man wrote back, \"I have hit upon one: that would be Ḵawlah bint Mismaʿ, aside from the size of her bosom.\" Thus, al-Ḥajjāj wrote to him, \"A woman's form is not good unless her breasts are full enough to warm up a bedmate and satiate a suckling.\""}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"trunk, torso"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"coat of mail measured to the torso"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"old man, aged man","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Nubian ibex (Capra nubiana syn. Capra jaela)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become fat"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become aged","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put a بَدَن (badan) around","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَدُنَ (baduna, “to be fat”)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of بَدَنَة (badana, “offered camel”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine plural of بَدِين (badīn, “fat”)","tags":["form-of","masculine","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ب د ن (b d n). Cognate with Mehri بدين."},"ipa":["/ba.dan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2014","headword_ar":"بَدُنَ","root":"bdn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badana","text_ar":"بَدَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S, M, Msb, K;) inf. n."},{"kind":"page_break","n":169},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaAnapN","text_ar":"بَدَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, &c.,) of the former, (ISk, T, S, &c.,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"budonN","text_ar":"بُدْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K,) also of the former, (ISk, T,) or of the latter, (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badonN","text_ar":"بَدْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) accord. to AZ, (T,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaAnN","text_ar":"بَدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buduwnN","text_ar":"بُدُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the inf. n. of the latter verb; (Msb;) said of a man, (ISk, T, S,) and of a camel; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badunato","text_ar":"بَدُنَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badanato","text_ar":"بَدَنَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a woman, (AZ, T, M, K,) and of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badanap","text_ar":"بَدَنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.; (Zj, T, &c.;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, big, bulky, big-bodied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corpulent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abounding in flesh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, T, M:) or the former verb has this last signification, that of fatness; and the latter verb is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~ana","text_ar":"بَدَّنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"q. v. (Ham p. 158.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"budonN","text_ar":"بُدْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","Mgh","Msb","K","ISk","AZ","Zj"]},{"entry_id":"n2015","headword_ar":"بدّن","root":"bdn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabodiynN","text_ar":"تَبْدِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, T, S, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, aged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and weak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was, or became, heavy by reason of age;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badana","text_ar":"بَدَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 158.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clad"},{"kind":"text","text":"a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badan","text_ar":"بَدَن"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diroE","text_ar":"دِرْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coat of mail"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K,* TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","Mgh","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n2016","headword_ar":"بُدْنٌ","root":"bdn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[properly an inf. n.; see 1:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fatness and compactness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"budunN","text_ar":"بُدُنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substance termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aHomN","text_ar":"شَحْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.)       -A2-  It is also a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badanapN","text_ar":"بَدَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, S, &c.:) ―         -b2-  and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdinN","text_ar":"بَادِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2017","headword_ar":"بَدَنٌ","root":"bdn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body, without the head and arms and legs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K;) so says Az: (Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body without the arms and legs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the shoulder-joint to the posteriors"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclusive"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA [as from the Mgh, in my copy of which it is not found]:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasada","text_ar":"جَسَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[generally meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body together with the members"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a man; (S;) often applied. to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whole of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasad","text_ar":"جَسَد"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Az, TA;) and in the Kur x. 92 it is said to mean the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body without soul:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodaAnN","text_ar":"اَبْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb;) whence the phrase, mentioned by Lh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahaA laHasanapu AlA^abodaAni","text_ar":"اـِنَّهَا لَحَسَنَةُ الاَبْدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily she is beautiful in respect of the body"},{"kind":"text","text":"], as though the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badanN","text_ar":"بَدَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"were applied to every portion of her. (M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$irokapu AlA^abodaAni","text_ar":"شِرْكَةُ الاَبْدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$irokapN biAlA^abodaAni","text_ar":"شِرْكَةٌ بِالاَبْدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Copartnership in bodily labours for the acquirement of gains."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a shirt, (Mgh, Msb,) and of a [garment of the kind called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~ap","text_ar":"جُبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that lies against the back and the belly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without the sleeves and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxaAriyS","text_ar":"دَخَارِيص"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gores with which it is widened"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh, Msb:) pl. as above. (Msb.) ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A short"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diroE","text_ar":"دِرْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coat of mail"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the measure of the body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or it is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a coat of mail"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diroE","text_ar":"دِرْع"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except that it is short, only such as covers the body, with short sleeves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diroE","text_ar":"دِرْع"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and so it is said to mean in the Kur x. 92 by IAar (T) and by Th; (M;) but Akh says that this assertion is of no account: (S:) pl. as above. (M, K.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~ap","text_ar":"جُبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as being likened to a coat of mail. (TA.) ―         -b5-  Accord. to Kr, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A limb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"member:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, specially, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limbs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"members, of a slaughtered camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K: [in the latter of which, the former of these two explanations is improperly connected with the first in this paragraph by the conjunction"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aw","text_ar":"او"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) to these he specially applies it in one instance: pl. as above. (M.) ―         -b6-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An old,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aged, man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN badanN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ بَدَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, S, M.) [In like manner, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdinN","text_ar":"بَادِنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badinN","text_ar":"بَدِنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are said by Golius, as on the authority of the S, to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"annosus et senior,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man, and also to a woman; but this explanation is wrong; and the latter word I do not find in any lexicon.] ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An old mountain-goat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEilN badanN","text_ar":"وَعِلٌ بَدَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) [in the present day,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badan","text_ar":"بَدَن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild goat of the Arabian and Egyptian deserts and mountains;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"capra jaela"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Hamilton Smith; called by some an"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ibex;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tayotal","text_ar":"تَيْتَل"},{"kind":"text","text":", properly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vayotalN","text_ar":"ثَيْتَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodunu","text_ar":"اَبْدُنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodanN","text_ar":"اَبْدَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buduwnN","text_ar":"بُدُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is extr. [with respect to rule], on the authority of IAar. (M, TA.) The rájiz says, describing a bitch (S, M) and a mountain-goat, (M, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qado qulotu lam~aA badati AlEuqaAbu\n                      \n                     \n                        waDam~ahaA waAlbadana AlHiqaAbN\n                      \n                     \n                        jid~iY likul~i EaAmilK vawaAbu\n                      \n                     \n                        Aalr~aA^osu waAlA^akoruEu waAlA_ihaAbu"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, * TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I had said, when El-' Ikáb appeared, and El-Hikáb comprised her and the old mountain-goat, “Exert thyself: for every worker"},{"kind":"text","text":"there is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a recompense: the head and the shanks and the hide"},{"kind":"text","text":"shall be thine”]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEqAb","text_ar":"العقاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of a bitch, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHqAb","text_ar":"الحقاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a certain mountain: he says, “Catch thou this goat, and I will make thy recompense to be the head and the shanks and the hide.” (TA.) [Hence Golius has been led to mistake"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHiqaAb","text_ar":"الحِقَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"for a signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albadanu","text_ar":"البَدَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b8-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lineage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parentage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grounds of pretension to respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","Mgh","S","M","K","T","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n2018","headword_ar":"بَدِنٌ","root":"bdn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badanN","text_ar":"بَدَنٌ"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2019","headword_ar":"بُدُنٌ","root":"bdn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"budonN","text_ar":"بُدْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  It is also a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badanapN","text_ar":"بَدَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K, &c.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}